readability_reflection: String concatenation was more readable due to it's more linear form which made it easier to follow.
comprehension_debugging: Interpolation took longer to understand because it had me looking back and forth from the guide.
preference_rationale: Concatenation for shorter strings, but interpolation for more complex stings. Interpolation would make it easier to make complex strings due to it's more modular form.
learning_curve: Not really. The only real impact my experience had was in recognizing where spaces were in the parenthesis.
suggestions_improvement: There are a couple of typos in the study which confused me a bit.
